defs.name: GraphQLQuery
defs.docs: A convenience trait that can be used to build a GraphQL request body.

attributes.value: / A convenience trait that can be used to build a GraphQL request body.
/ This will be implemented for you by codegen in the normal case. It is implemented on the struct you place the derive on.

defs.name: Variables
defs.docs: The shape of the variables expected by the query. This should be a generated struct most of the time.

attributes.value: / The shape of the variables expected by the query. This should be a generated struct most of the time.

defs.name: ResponseData
defs.docs: The top-level shape of the response data (the `data` field in the GraphQL response). In practice this should be generated, since it is hard to write by hand without error.

attributes.value: / The top-level shape of the response data (the `data` field in the GraphQL response). In practice this should be generated, since it is hard to write by hand without error.

defs.name: build_query
defs.docs: Produce a GraphQL query struct that can be JSON serialized and sent to a GraphQL API.

attributes.value: / Produce a GraphQL query struct that can be JSON serialized and sent to a GraphQL API.

defs.name: QueryBody
defs.docs: The form in which queries are sent over HTTP in most implementations. This will be built using the [`GraphQLQuery`] trait normally.

attributes.value: / The form in which queries are sent over HTTP in most implementations. This will be built using the [`GraphQLQuery`] trait normally.

defs.name: variables
defs.docs: The values for the variables. They must match those declared in the queries. This should be the `Variables` struct from the generated module corresponding to the query.
